# What is a Version Control System?

* A System that... Controls Versions.
* Stores your files, be they text or binary
* Keeps track of who did what and when


# Why should I care?

* Answers the oft-asked question: "Who the hell did that?"
* Answers the oft-asked question: "When the hell did that happen?"
* Lets you jump to any point in time
* Lets you see what changed between versions
* You can review your work *before* it takes effect
* You can play nice with others
* Keeps the auditors happy
* Keeps the doctor away


# What is git?

* A Distributed Version Control System
